Then, get the current music trends on YouTube Music for the United States. After that, search for the classical composer Ludovico Einaudi on SoundCloud, limiting results to the top 10 users. Finally, I'd like to listen to the Emisora Radio Dosis mix stream.
simple_rewrite: I'm doing some music research across different platforms for a project. Could you pull up the Billboard 200 albums chart from March 15, 2023? I'd also like to see what's currently trending on YouTube Music in the United States. While we're at it, can you look up the classical composer Ludovico Einaudi on SoundCloud, but just show me the top 10 users? To wrap things up, I'd love to tune into the Emisora Radio Dosis mix stream for some background music while I review all this information.
hard_rewrite: I'm exploring the musical landscape of early 2023 and wondering what albums were making waves in mid-March. Also curious about which artists are currently capturing America's attention on streaming platforms. I've been hearing about this Italian pianist who composes minimalist contemporary classical pieces - I think his last name starts with 'E' - and would love to discover who's sharing his work on that orange-logoed audio platform. To wind down my musical journey, I'd like to immerse myself in a continuous stream of curated sounds from that Latin American radio station with 'Dosis' in its name.

query: I'm working on a music industry research project and need some help gathering data from different sources. Could you pull up the top artists on YouTube for 2023, including featured artists in music videos? I'm also curious about which music videos reached the 1 billion view milestone fastest on YouTube. For the US market specifically, I'd like to check which albums were charting on the Billboard 200 as of November 15, 2023. To expand my research globally, could you provide an alphabetical list of 200 countries so I can explore international radio stations through the Radio World database? Lastly, I'm looking for a children's album called 'Sing Along' - I need access to its songs and lyrics.

Additionally, show me today's trending artists on Genius Leaderboard, get details for the Shazam song with key 40333609, and generate a radio playlist based on The Weeknd (Spotify URI: spotify:artist:1Xyo4u8uXC1ZmMpatF05PJ) who was popular during this time.

Show me the top English-language music videos on YouTube in the past 24 hours. Look up Halsey's albums on Spotify using artist ID '1Xyo4u8uXC1ZmMpatF05PJ'. Search for information about artist Dua Lipa. Stream music from Emisora Radio Dosis. Get the YouTube Music watch playlist for Billie Eilish's 'bad guy' (video ID 'DyDfgMOUjCI'). Finally, search for BTS's song 'Dynamite' on Shazam, limiting to 5 results in English (en-US).

I'd love to see her album information and maybe read a random song excerpt. Also, I'm curious about what's trending right now - can you check which music videos are popular on YouTube in Korea and which English-language music videos have the most views in the past 24 hours? I'd also appreciate discovering some random radio stations from around the world (just 5 stations would be enough) and maybe streaming something from Emisora Radio Dosis. While we're at it, could you pull up The Weeknd's album discography on Spotify? I'm also interested in learning more about Dua Lipa, and I was wondering if you could search for BTS's song 'Dynamite' using Shazam (just 5 results in English would be fine). Oh, and one last thing - I'd like to access a YouTube Music watch playlist for the video with ID 'DyDfgMOUjCI'.

I'm also interested in what's currently capturing attention in Korea's music scene on YouTube, and which English-language videos are getting the most views right now. Oh, and there's this YouTube Music video with the code 'DyDfgMOUjCI' that I'd like to check out the playlist for.

task_description: Complete the requested task using the available tools
refined_query: Show me the top artists on YouTube for 2022 and the most streamed songs on Spotify in 2022. Then get the Billboard Global 200 chart rankings for May 20, 2023, and retrieve trending tracks from Shazam in English (en-US). Also, list all songs by Halsey, and get detailed information about Ed Sheeran's 'Photograph' on SoundCloud. Finally, search YouTube Music for 'Taylor Swift latest' and retrieve song details for the YouTube video with ID 4NRXx6U8ABQ.
simple_rewrite: I'm putting together a music presentation about recent trends and need some help with research. Could you look up popular music from 2022 across different platforms? I'd like to know who the top YouTube artists were, which songs got the most streams on Spotify, and how songs ranked on the recent Billboard Global 200 chart. Also, can you check what's been trending on Shazam lately? I'm particularly interested in finding information about Halsey and Taylor Swift. Oh, and I also need some specific details about Ed Sheeran's song 'Photograph' on SoundCloud.
hard_rewrite: I've been wondering about the music scene from a couple of years ago. What was capturing everyone's attention back in 2022? I'm curious about which artists dominated YouTube views that year, and which songs people couldn't stop streaming on Spotify. Also, what tracks were making waves globally around May last year? I've heard some friends talking about discovering new music through Shazam - what's been trending there? I'm particularly interested in what Halsey has been creating lyrically. And speaking of artists, how has Taylor Swift been performing on platforms? Oh, and I recently heard Ed Sheeran's 'Photograph' on SoundCloud and was captivated - I'd love to know more about that specific track's details.

query: I'm doing some music research across different platforms and would love your help. Could you show me Billboard's top 10 greatest artists of all time? I'm also curious about which Vietnamese artists have the highest view counts on YouTube. Speaking of artists, I'm a big fan of Halsey - could you pull up her complete discography with all her albums and share a random excerpt from one of her songs? I'd also be interested in learning about which top YouTube artists from 2022 were involved in collaborations. On a more specific note, can you look up information about this particular Spotify track with ID 4WNcduiCmDNfmTEz7JvmLv? While we're discussing music services, what can you tell me about Radio Dosis Mix streaming service? Oh, and I'd appreciate if you could search for BTS on YouTube Music with comprehensive results - let's say about 40 results. Lastly, what kind of information is accessible through the Kooed radio stations endpoint?

Finally, I'd like a random Halsey song and search results for 'Despacito remix', as well as this month's top albums on Genius, with 20 results on the first page.

I'd love to see the latest music releases on Spotify in the US, along with what's currently charting on the Billboard Global chart (excluding US) for June 10, 2023. I'm particularly interested in K-pop lately - can you pull up some information about the girl group Twice? I've been looking at MusicData API's YouTube weekly tool that tracked popular music videos during the 21st week of 2019, as well as their feature showing top YouTube artists for 2022. I've also explored Radio World's search function that displayed 20 jazz stations in ascending order, and used MusiclinkssApi to look up information about composer 'Ennio Morricone'. Additionally, I've come across Miza's tool that breaks down YouTube playlist data, Shazam's feature that pulls song details using key '40333609' with US English locale, MusiclinkssApi's capability to analyze Taylor Swift's Spotify artist page URL, and Spotify's global daily top 200 songs chart. Based on all these different data sources, what patterns might emerge across these music platforms, and what insights could we draw about current music consumption and popularity trends?
hard_rewrite: I've been analyzing some music industry data and noticed some interesting patterns across different platforms. Looking at the weekly YouTube trends from that period right before summer 2019, alongside the featured artist rankings from a couple years ago, I'm curious about what these tell us about listener preferences. I also found some jazz radio station listings, and information about that legendary Italian film composer known for spaghetti westerns. There's also data from a specific YouTube playlist I've been monitoring, details about that famous piano piece that's in every emotional movie scene (you know, the one with the flowing water title), and information about that pop star who recently re-recorded all her early albums. The global daily streaming charts round out my collection. What meaningful connections or trends might emerge when examining all these different music consumption patterns together?

query: I'm doing a deep dive into music trends from 2019 for a research project. Could you help me gather some information? I'd like to see who the top YouTube artists were that year, along with Billboard's Artist 100 chart specifically from March 18, 2019. I'm particularly interested in classical music too - would you mind looking up Ludovico Einaudi's albums on SoundCloud, but just the first 10 results? Also, could you pull all his albums from Spotify using his artist ID 2uFUBdaVGtyMqckSeCl0Qj? I'm curious about international charts as well, so I'd appreciate seeing the top 20 songs from Billboard Japan's Hot 100 from May 11, 2019. For my background listening while researching, could you find me about 15 classical radio stations, listed in ascending order? Oh, and I'd love some background information on the composer Ennio Morricone, plus a way to stream Radio Dosis Mix while I work.

Then, find songs by the composer 'bellman' and radio stations in Indonesia. I want to get detailed metadata for Ed Sheeran's 'Photograph' on SoundCloud with high-quality download options. Also, retrieve information about YouTube Music user 'UC44hbeRoCZVVMVg5z0FfIww' and the lyrics for Owl City's 'The Saltwater Room' from SoundCloud. Additionally, search Spotify for the top 15 tracks related to 'summer dance party' and get complete details about the YouTube Music song with video ID 'dvgZkm1xWPE'.
simple_rewrite: I'm putting together a music playlist and need some help with research. Could you share Billboard's top 5 Greatest Songs of the Summer of all time? I'm also interested in discovering compositions by 'bellman' and browsing radio stations available in Indonesia. For a specific track I love, can you pull up detailed metadata for Ed Sheeran's 'Photograph' on SoundCloud, including any high-quality download options? While you're at it, I'd appreciate information about the YouTube Music user with the ID 'UC44hbeRoCZVVMVg5z0FfIww' and the lyrics to Owl City's 'The Saltwater Room' from SoundCloud. To round things out, would you mind searching Spotify for the top 15 tracks related to 'summer dance party' and providing complete details about the YouTube Music song with video ID 'dvgZkm1xWPE'?
hard_rewrite: I've been thinking about creating a summer playlist that brings back nostalgic vibes. I wonder what Billboard considers the ultimate summer anthems of all time - just the top handful would be interesting. There's also this Swedish composer with a name that sounds like 'bellman' who wrote some beautiful melodies I'd like to explore. I'm planning a trip to Southeast Asia and would love to tune into some local radio while I'm there, particularly in the country known for Bali and Jakarta. I recently heard Ed Sheeran's emotional track about memories and photographs on SoundCloud and wanted to save it in the best quality possible. There's this YouTube Music channel with a cryptic ID 'UC44hbeRoCZVVMVg5z0FfIww' that I stumbled upon - what kind of content do they actually share? I'm also trying to find the poetic lyrics to that Owl City song about an ocean room with salt water. For my upcoming beach party, I need some upbeat tracks - maybe searching Spotify for 'summer dance party' would give me good inspiration? Finally, there's this YouTube Music video with ID 'dvgZkm1xWPE' that someone recommended, but I'd like to know more details about it before adding it to my collection.

query: I'm doing a deep dive into music analytics for a project. Could you help me research music trends by looking up Billboard's Greatest of All Time Artists (just the top 10), and also check what's currently trending on Spotify's US home page? I'm particularly interested in examining Ed Sheeran's 'Photograph' on SoundCloud - can you pull the detailed metadata for that? Also, I need to reference the Billboard 200 chart specifically from March 18, 2020. While you're at it, could you find Radiohead's user profile information on Spotify and gather comprehensive details about this specific song on Shazam (key: 552406075)? For the creative part of my project, I'd like to take Daft Punk's 'Get Lucky' YouTube video and extend it into a 45-minute version, plus create a single MP3 playlist that combines three massive hits: 'See You Again', 'Despacito', and 'Shape of You'.

tool_list.tool description: Trims a song or video to specified start and end times, returning a URL that requires a GET request to retrieve the actual output. Specify trim points in seconds or time formats like '2h30m', with the option to omit either by using an empty string or dash (-). The function can automatically extend content by looping when trim end exceeds the original duration, making it significantly faster than concatenating multiple copies for creating extended versions of media. This endpoint is part of a multipurpose API offering various image, video, and audio operations, allowing for efficient media manipulation without the need for re-encoding each segment.

refined_query: Show me information about popular music artists and songs from different sources. I want to see Billboard's top 10 greatest artists of all time, YouTube Music trends in Germany, information about the K-pop idol Jungkook, songs by the artist Thorbjørn Egner, songs composed by Bellman, some random radio stations, weekly and monthly charts from Genius, details about the K-pop song 'Spring Day', and create a 45-minute extended version of the YouTube song at https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IgOci6JXPIc in MP3 format.
simple_rewrite: I'm doing some music research for a project and need to gather information from various sources. Could you help me find Billboard's top 10 greatest artists of all time and check what's trending on YouTube Music in Germany right now? I'm also interested in learning about the K-pop idol Jungkook and would love details about the K-pop song 'Spring Day'. Can you pull up songs by Thorbjørn Egner and compositions by Bellman? I'd appreciate if you could suggest some random radio stations to listen to and show me both weekly and monthly charts from Genius. Finally, I came across this YouTube song at https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IgOci6JXPIc that I really enjoy - would it be possible to create a 45-minute extended version of it in MP3 format?
hard_rewrite: I'm exploring the music world and feeling curious about legendary artists across different genres. Could you help me discover who's considered among the all-time greats according to Billboard's historical rankings? Also, I'm interested in what German music fans are currently enjoying on YouTube. My friend from South Korea keeps mentioning someone named Jungkook - what's his background? I recently heard some charming Scandinavian children's songs by someone called Thorbjørn Egner and also some classical Swedish pieces attributed to Bellman - could you find anything about those? I'd love to discover some new radio stations to broaden my horizons. What artists are trending this month according to Genius? There's also this Korean song called 'Spring Day' that everyone's talking about - what can you tell me about it? Finally, I found this beautiful melody on YouTube (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IgOci6JXPIc) that I wish lasted longer - about 45 minutes would be perfect for my meditation practice. Is there a way to make that happen in MP3 format?

query: I'm doing some music research for a project. Could you pull up the Billboard Hot 100 chart for November 25, 2023, along with the Independent Albums chart from that same date? I'm also interested in finding radio stations in Indonesia. While you're at it, could you show me all of Halsey's albums and dig up some information about composer Ennio Morricone? I also need details about a specific Spotify track with ID 4WNcduiCmDNfmTEz7JvmLv. Oh, and would you mind showing me what mood categories exist for music in German? Lastly, I want to combine two audio pieces - the YouTube video at https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0zXcC-haBFc and the audio file at http://i.mizabot.xyz/d/Bc5SdZDrKg - and then convert the combined result to OGG format.
